Pallekala, Rao 1\:54 PM hey Adrian Krygowski, Adrian 1\:54 PM hey rao Pallekala, Rao 1\:55 PM I checked the database why it was returning 3 entries for 10.12.61.153 Krygowski, Adrian 1\:55 PM yeah Pallekala, Rao 1\:56 PM This IP is configured twice as Virtual Switch with two different names Krygowski, Adrian 1\:56 PM is that a UK config? Pallekala, Rao 1\:56 PM and once as regular Switch with no domain ID Yes Not sure if it is data issue Krygowski, Adrian 1\:58 PM ok, so i can expect similar response from UK switches multiple IPs, differnt names/domainIds Pallekala, Rao 1\:59 PM I think so... but I am not domain expert, what ever is in Data warehouse I am sending to you Krygowski, Adrian 1\:59 PM who decided how to document the switch in the Data Warehouse? just wondering? and thanks for the explanation Pallekala, Rao 2\:02 PM NetApp puts that data in warehouse, I am not sure if there are any documents that explain on how they populate the warehouse, but the database has comments that says what is column is Krygowski, Adrian 2\:03 PM ok... well if its somewhat automated, then i can expect the same for all UK switches then Pallekala, Rao 2\:04 PM I think we need to expect same type of data in Prod as well. I see same IP with different names in Prod as well UKSLOU1-003-BDCX-UTILITY 10.55.4.208 2 ZZLO1 UKSLOU1-003-BDCX 10.55.4.208 128 ZZLO1 UKSLOU1-004-BDCX-UTILITY 10.55.4.211 2 ZZLO1 UKSLOU1-004-BDCX 10.55.4.211 2 ZZLO1 Krygowski, Adrian 2\:04 PM yeah these are UK Pallekala, Rao 2\:04 PM defrft4-001-brfs 10.88.0.200 1 ZZFR4 defrft4-002-brfs 10.88.0.201 1 ZZFR4 Krygowski, Adrian 2\:05 PM different IPs in france germany Pallekala, Rao 2\:05 PM UKLOND6-003-BDCX-UTILITY 10.83.100.214 2 ZZLOND UKLOND6-003-BDCX 10.83.100.214 128 ZZLOND Krygowski, Adrian 2\:05 PM ok yeah thanks Rao this makes sense now fbcf5f44-cc0f-4305-8bcb-af2b6a0839fd.55a16879-baa5-4dc7-a60f-da1749f0ddbe.description=
Snopsis\: Scriptlet that grabs all keys and out puts only keys that have Local values.  This is to emulate an ARGV type functionality.  Will only provide inputs of direct flow calling this operation.

Inputs\: None

Results\:
All local variables in argv format\: "index1\=value1 index2\=value2a+value2b index3\=value3a,value3b,value3c..."
Internal variables that can be potentially disregaurded\: (example was runCLU)
username
execution_thread_id
RS_Previous_Transition
webserviceHost
errorDetails
Result
RS_Previous_Response
password
flowUuid
webservicePort

Responses\:
failure - Something went wrong
success - Built argv list
fbcf5f44-cc0f-4305-8bcb-af2b6a0839fd.55e8e4b4-0575-45f9-b378-044d4a010f8b.description=
Service to perform an HTTP GET via the Java HTTP Client

Inputs\:
url - the url to attempt to retrieve.
username - the username to authenticate to url with.
password - the password for username.
timeout - a timeout after which the connection should be terminated, or 0 for no timeout.
useCookies - Enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. valid options are\: true/false
followRedirects - specifies whether or not the get command should automatically follow redirects.
trustAllRoots - enables weak security over SSL. A SSH certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it. valid options are\: true/false
proxy - a proxy to use when accessing the web site.
proxyPort - a port on the proxy to connect to.
proxyUsername - a username to use when connecting to the proxy.
proxyPassword - a password to use when connecting to the proxy.
encodeURL - perform URL encoding.

Responses\:
success - URL retrieved successfully.
failure - The url could not be retrieved.
